    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Small, short nails with broad heads, designed to nail leathers to wood. Examples of use are nailing leather onto scuppers, which are holes on ships or other locations to allow water run-off, or to attach leathers to blacksmith bellows.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
